This position is based in our Gangnam office, reporting to the Head of APAC, Regulatory &amp; International Legal.
You Will:

Advise on existing, pending, and developing regulations affecting Roblox, including regulations concerning online UGC platforms and consumer protection issues in Korea; 
Identify new trends in the regulations and educate company leadership on their implications;
Help create a cross-functional response to legal obligations; 
Develop and implement procedures, policies and programs to ensure Roblox compliance with applicable laws and regulations in Korea
Analyze complex legal issues and translate analysis into practical advice;
Evaluate, engage, and oversee outside counsel in Korea;
Liaise and develop strong relationships with relevant regulators in Korea;
Provide legal advice and support in relation to local content ratings issues;
Respond to requests for compliance advice from engineering, product and marketing teams concerning time-sensitive communications and product releases.

You Have: 

8+ years PQE with a top tier Korean or international law firm and/or tech corporation (e.g. gaming, online safety, privacy, social media, content regulations) 
Strong business-oriented judgment and the ability to analyze problems, propose resolutions, and provide advice that is creative, practical, and legally acceptable, taking into account the needs and objectives of the business;
Licensed to practice law in Korea
Excellent written and oral communication skills in English
Ability to work well with a small, tightly knit team and desire to seek responsibility and work autonomously. Must be able to manage a diverse and complex workload while maintaining priorities and proactively anticipating issues
Experience assessing, analyzing and resolving multiple risk management-related issues and challenges in a fast-paced, dynamic organization, with limited supervision
Experience with applicable regulatory requirements and identifying emerging trends.
Track record of interfacing with cross-functional leadership to solve problems and manage complex issues.
